__________________________________

Spending the day today practicing this technique. It’s been 8 years since I did the first style keychains. 

They are for sure my favorite because they are made 100% by me in my shop.

Although it  does take a bit of practice to get the sequence down. Also using stainless this time so that means it needs to be hotter and I have to hit it harder.

The process goes like this.
-Material is cut to maximum length for my forge and heated to 2000°
-I hammer flats on the diamond with my Turkish power hammer.
-Then I stamp the logo on each flat.
-Then to the anvil to take the curve out of the material and hand hammer a flat in between each flat.
-Next to the Ironworker to pierce a hole between each flat centered on the flat spot I just hammered.
-finally they are parted off at a 45° angle so the end can be used as a bottle opener.
-Finally into the tumbler to knock the edges off and put a burnished finish on.

You really have to Focus and Boogie to get all these steps done in one heat!

It took me 4 or 5 bars to get my rhythm
Back down.

I used my @payupsucker stamp to practice, but I’m working on a new cool/funny stamp for the Contest keychains.

The contest officially Launches August 1st. But im going to keep the $25 pre-order deal going for a couple more days.

If you want one, or Five!

PayPal me $25 (friends/family)

—> Popeofwelding@jjfu.com 

Make sure you put Full Name and Shipping Address in the notes!

If you already ordered, Thank you! Better order a couple more for better odds!

Sweet!

@popeofwelding 
#jessejames

node.text:
.......
After all these years if pretty proud that I still refuse to fake or stage anything on the show. Drama will always come organically if you wait for it.
If we make it, we make it. 
If we fail, we fail. 

Here’s a cell phone video shot of the badass Delorean Hovercraft team making it work with 30 seconds left!
Yea I had to get pissed and ride them hard the whole week. But in the end? They made one of the best builds in the history of the show! 

Congrats guys enjoy those @snapon_official Tools!

You can check out this episode and all the others Now on @discoveryplus 

#jessejames
#monstergarage

node.text:
Sooo this is my quarterly “proud papa” post…

Since my 17yo daughter Sunny has kind of out grown going to summer camp every year. 
I had an idea to see how she would do tattooing. She is an Amazing artist. She spends a ton of time sketching, painting, drawing.
So I hit up my sweetheart friend @little0ne in Monterey California to see if she would be into a month of Free slave labor!. Jen welcomed her with open arms at the shop @divine.rituals 
All I can say is my hunch was right!
Sunny took to tattooing like a fish to water. She spent about 5 days cleaning, making stencils and prepping machines and practicing. Then they put her in a chair and she started taking walk in customers. The fact that her very first paying tattoo on a customer was “DEEZ NUTS” is Pure Legend! Her work is very clean and everyone says she got “it”. Her and Jen also went up to Reno for a couple days and saw legendary tattoo artist @classicjuan He gave her some really great advice and pointers. 
What a great trip she had.
She also came home with a brand new shiny Moth tattoo by Jen and some money in her pocket. 
Nothing better!
Next steps are finding a shop here in Austin she can apprentice the next year while she’s in her senior year of High School. I love seeing her find her “thing”. Very proud.

I also want to thank Jen @little0ne for being key to make all this happen. You opened your home and shop and life to Sunny and gave her such a positive female based experience. I’ll love you forever for this! Also thanks to the crew at @divine.rituals for being so cool and welcoming to her. And thank you @classicjuan for the tutoring and advice. It for sure stuck!

Now I just need @nikkohurtado and @guyaitchisonart to come finish some work on me and sneak in some schooling for Sunny! 

That’s it, proud beaming papa. I sure love my baby girl.

#jessejames
@popeofwelding

It’s such a treat to work on my friends cars! 
My buddy Matt ( @matthewmuss ) just picked up this clean clean ‘62 from Boris at @streetmachinery 
Small problem is the OG style long tube headers on the Rat motor hung too low. When you car was laid out the headers hit first. We put some cast manifolds and built a nice nice tucked up stainless system with @magnaflow mufflers. Now the car can lay all the way down and nothing hits. 
Just as it should!

#jessejames
@popeofwelding

node.text:
I love this quote. Hits very close to home for me lately……

 “I can’t spend time with people I don’t enjoy. I can’t do it anymore as theater. I make choices, and that’s a beautiful thing about growing up, learning to say no, in a nice way, just say no. I have this friend…we just went different ways in life. Once he came to me and said, “Francis, you don’t like me anymore.” and I said “No, it’s not that I don’t like you, we’ve chosen different styles of life. I still have beautiful souvenirs of all the things we did together and how close we were, but the truth is it’s not that you bore me, but I don’t enjoy talking to you anymore and I don’t want to fight with you but there’s nothing in common between your life and mine nowadays”. I would have never said that but he asked me. So what could I say? I said the truth. Growing up has a bit to do with that, to be able to tell the truth, to show who you are, even if it hurts.”

~Francis Mallmann
(👉🏽 @francismallmann )

( 📸 @hameisterphoto )

But yea I love him! 

#jessejames

__________________________________

Spending the day today practicing this technique. It’s been 8 years since I did the first style keychains. 

They are for sure my favorite because they are made 100% by me in my shop.

Although it  does take a bit of practice to get the sequence down. Also using stainless this time so that means it needs to be hotter and I have to hit it harder.

The process goes like this.
-Material is cut to maximum length for my forge and heated to 2000°
-I hammer flats on the diamond with my Turkish power hammer.
-Then I stamp the logo on each flat.
-Then to the anvil to take the curve out of the material and hand hammer a flat in between each flat.
-Next to the Ironworker to pierce a hole between each flat centered on the flat spot I just hammered.
-finally they are parted off at a 45° angle so the end can be used as a bottle opener.
-Finally into the tumbler to knock the edges off and put a burnished finish on.

You really have to Focus and Boogie to get all these steps done in one heat!

It took me 4 or 5 bars to get my rhythm
Back down.

I used my @payupsucker stamp to practice, but I’m working on a new cool/funny stamp for the Contest keychains.

The contest officially Launches August 1st. But im going to keep the $25 pre-order deal going for a couple more days.

If you want one, or Five!

PayPal me $25 (friends/family)

—> Popeofwelding@jjfu.com 

Make sure you put Full Name and Shipping Address in the notes!

If you already ordered, Thank you! Better order a couple more for better odds!

Sweet!

@popeofwelding 
#jessejames

So this whole year I’ve been doing 2 weeks on Gunsmithing and switching to 2 weeks on Fab work. 
Seems to be working pretty good. I’m making progress on everything. It’s a little mentally tough because of the 2 week gap. So stuff like this copper gas tank for @danawhite seems like it’s taking longer than it’s suppose to. Until I look back at pics from a few weeks ago and it didn’t exist. It was still flat copper sheet metal. I guess since my head I already knows what it’s going to look like, my eyes only want to see the finished product. Patience is key. Once it’s done I can move on to the front fender and exhaust system.
Should be able to knock this tank out in the next 2 week stint that starts a week from Monday . So my focus this week and next week is finishing some guns.
Oh yea! I forgot I have to squeeze in my Damascus forging in there somewhere.
We really need to get the days increased to 30 hours. 
That way I could get more done.

@popeofwelding 
#jessejames
